2 Load inputs

2.1 Load meta analysis results

> file = list.files(path = OUTFOLDER, pattern = "S01.MONSTER_Meta_analysis.", full.names = T)
> 
> newest_file = file[order(file.mtime(file), decreasing = T)][1]
> print(basename(newest_file))
[1] "S01.MONSTER_Meta_analysis.2021-01-27.csv"
> # load the newest data
> meta = read.csv(newest_file)

2.2 Load combined PValues

> file = list.files(path = OUTFOLDER, pattern = "S01.combined_MONSTER_PValues.", full.names = T)
> 
> newest_file = file[order(file.mtime(file), decreasing = T)][1]
> print(basename(newest_file))
[1] "S01.combined_MONSTER_PValues.2021-01-27.csv"
> # load the newest data
> assoc = read.csv(newest_file)

2.2.1 format assoc

> assoc.long = assoc %>% select(CurrentGene, Asian_PValue, African_PValue, Hispanic_PValueGC, 
+     Eur01A_PValue, Eur01B_PValue, Eur01C_PValue, Eur01D_PValue, Eur02A_PValue, Eur02B_PValueGC, 
+     Eur03A_PValue, Eur03B_PValue, Eur04_PValue, Eur05A_PValue, Eur05B_PValue, Eur05C_PValue) %>% 
+     pivot_longer(col = -CurrentGene, names_to = "cohort.tmp", values_to = "P") %>% 
+     separate(col = cohort.tmp, into = c("cohort", "metric"), sep = "_") %>% group_by(cohort) %>% 
+     mutate(P_FDR = p.adjust(P, method = "BH"))

2.3 Load gene overview

> gene_overview = read.delim(paste0(INPUTFOLDER, "genes_overview.txt"))

3 QC

3.1 Correlations between SNP numbers included in MONSTER analysis for gene and PValues

3.1.1 get SNP numbers

> snp.num.long = assoc %>% select(CurrentGene, ends_with("Num_Variants")) %>% pivot_longer(col = -CurrentGene, 
+     names_to = "cohort.tmp", values_to = "SNP.Num") %>% mutate(cohort = str_extract(string = cohort.tmp, 
+     pattern = "^[0-9A-Za-z]+")) %>% select(-cohort.tmp)
> 
> # correction of typo
> snp.num.long[snp.num.long$cohort == "Afrian", ]$cohort = "African"

3.1.2 calculate correlation

> cor.data = assoc.long %>% left_join(snp.num.long) %>% # remove missing data points
+ filter(!is.na(P)) %>% group_by(cohort) %>% summarise(Corr = cor(x = -log10(P), y = SNP.Num)) %>% 
+     arrange(-Corr)
> myDT(cor.data)

3.1.3 Plot

> assoc.long %>% left_join(snp.num.long) %>% # remove missing data points
+ filter(!is.na(P)) %>% group_by(cohort) %>% ggplot(aes(x = -log10(P), y = SNP.Num, 
+     color = cohort)) + geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE) + facet_wrap(~cohort, 
+     scales = "free", ncol = 3) + my_ggplotTheme + ggsave(paste0(OUTFOLDER, SCRIPT, 
+     ".supp.correlation_numberSNPs_and_PValue.", DATE, ".pdf"), device = "pdf", dpi = 300, 
+     height = 10)

3.2 Meta-Analysis

For overall Meta-Analysis remove genes with more than half of cohorts missing (Number_missingPvalues>8) or for European only Meta-Analysis more than half of European cohorts missing (Number_missingPvalues>6)

> meta.qc = meta %>% mutate(QC_flag.missing_all = ifelse(Number_missingPvalues > 8, 
+     "YES", "NO"), QC_flag.missing_european = ifelse(Number_missingPvalues > 6, "YES", 
+     "NO"))

3.2.1 How many and which genes removed?

3.2.1.1 Meta-Analysis all (YES = ‘more than half cohorts with missing result’ | NO = ‘all good’)

> meta.qc %>% count(QC_flag.missing_all)
# A tibble: 2 x 2
  QC_flag.missing_all     n
  <chr>               <int>
1 NO                  17960
2 YES                   701

3.2.1.2 Meta-Analysis European (YES = ‘more than half cohorts with missing result’ | NO = ‘all good’)

> meta.qc %>% count(QC_flag.missing_european)
# A tibble: 2 x 2
  QC_flag.missing_european     n
  <chr>                    <int>
1 NO                       17951
2 YES                        710

4 Top Hits

4.1 Meta-Analysis all (FDR corrected Meta-Analysis PValue < 0.05)

> hits.meta.all = meta.qc %>% filter(QC_flag.missing_all == "NO") %>% filter(StoufferMetaP_FDR < 
+     0.05) %>% arrange(StoufferMetaP_FDR) %>% mutate(Hit = "meta.all.fdr.p")
> hits.meta.all %>% select(-StoufferMetaEuropeanP, -StoufferMetaEuropeanP_FDR) %>% 
+     myDT()

4.2 Meta-Analysis european (FDR corrected Meta-Analysis PValue < 0.05)

> hits.meta.euro = meta.qc %>% filter(QC_flag.missing_european == "NO") %>% filter(StoufferMetaEuropeanP_FDR < 
+     0.05) %>% arrange(StoufferMetaEuropeanP_FDR) %>% mutate(Hit = "meta.european.fdr.p")
> hits.meta.euro %>% select(-StoufferMetaP, -StoufferMetaP_FDR) %>% myDT()

4.3 Asian ancestry

4.3.1 FDR corrected PValue < 0.05 -> NONE

> assoc.long %>% filter(cohort == "Asian") %>% filter(P_FDR < 0.05)
# A tibble: 0 x 5
# Groups:   cohort [0]
# … with 5 variables: CurrentGene <fct>, cohort <chr>, metric <chr>, P <dbl>,
#   P_FDR <dbl>

4.3.2 uncorrected PValue < 1e-4

> hits.asian = assoc.long %>% filter(cohort == "Asian") %>% filter(P < 1e-04)

4.4 African ancestry

4.4.1 FDR corrected PValue < 0.05 -> NONE

> assoc.long %>% filter(cohort == "African") %>% filter(P_FDR < 0.05)
# A tibble: 0 x 5
# Groups:   cohort [0]
# … with 5 variables: CurrentGene <fct>, cohort <chr>, metric <chr>, P <dbl>,
#   P_FDR <dbl>

4.4.2 uncorrected PValue < 1e-4

> hits.african = assoc.long %>% filter(cohort == "African") %>% filter(P < 1e-04)

4.5 Hispanic ancestry

4.5.1 FDR corrected PValue < 0.05 -> NONE

> assoc.long %>% filter(cohort == "Hispanic") %>% filter(P_FDR < 0.05)
# A tibble: 0 x 5
# Groups:   cohort [0]
# … with 5 variables: CurrentGene <fct>, cohort <chr>, metric <chr>, P <dbl>,
#   P_FDR <dbl>

4.5.2 uncorrected PValue < 1e-4 , also NONE

> hits.hispanic = assoc.long %>% filter(cohort == "Hispanic") %>% filter(P < 1e-04)

4.6 Combine hit results

4.6.1 Format inputs

> hits.meta.all.format = hits.meta.all %>% mutate(cohort = "meta.all") %>% select(cohort, 
+     CurrentGene, Hit, P = StoufferMetaP_FDR)
> 
> hits.meta.euro.format = hits.meta.euro %>% mutate(cohort = "meta.euro") %>% select(cohort, 
+     CurrentGene, Hit, P = StoufferMetaEuropeanP_FDR)
> 
> hits.asian.format = hits.asian %>% mutate(Hit = "single.asian.uncorrP.1e-4") %>% 
+     select(CurrentGene, Hit, P)
> 
> hits.african.format = hits.african %>% mutate(Hit = "single.african.uncorrP.1e-4") %>% 
+     select(CurrentGene, Hit, P)

4.6.2 Combine

> hit.list = list(hits.meta.all.format, hits.meta.euro.format, hits.asian.format, hits.african.format)
> Hits = data.table::rbindlist(hit.list)

4.8 Save

5 Overlap between cohorts

5.1 extend hit data with Pvalues from all cohort and respective ranks

5.1.1 format single assoc results

> hit_genes = unique(Hits$CurrentGene)
> 
> assoc.hits = assoc.long %>% group_by(cohort) %>% mutate(P_rank = frank(P, na.last = "keep")) %>% 
+     filter(CurrentGene %in% hit_genes) %>% select(CurrentGene, cohort, metric, P, 
+     P_rank)

5.1.2 format meta analysis results

> meta.hits = meta.qc %>% filter(QC_flag.missing_all == "NO" & QC_flag.missing_european == 
+     "NO") %>% select(CurrentGene, StoufferMetaP_FDR, StoufferMetaEuropeanP_FDR) %>% 
+     pivot_longer(col = -CurrentGene, names_to = "metric", values_to = "P") %>% mutate(cohort = ifelse(metric == 
+     "StoufferMetaP_FDR", "meta.all", "meta.euro")) %>% group_by(cohort) %>% mutate(P_rank = frank(P, 
+     na.last = "keep")) %>% filter(CurrentGene %in% hit_genes) %>% select(CurrentGene, 
+     cohort, metric, P, P_rank)

5.1.3 combine all

> hits.extended = assoc.hits %>% rbind(meta.hits) %>% left_join(Hits[, -"P"], by = c("CurrentGene", 
+     "cohort")) %>% mutate(is_a_hit = ifelse(is.na(Hit), "NO", "YES"))

5.1.4 add number of significant analyses and median rank

> hits.gene.summary = hits.extended %>% group_by(CurrentGene) %>% summarise(MedianRank = median(P_rank, 
+     na.rm = T), NumberHitAnalyses = sum(!is.na(Hit)))
> hits.gene.summary %>% arrange(MedianRank) %>% myDT

7 Add overlap with previous BCAC GWAS results

7.1 Did BCAC also report our findings?

7.1.1 Creating Locuszoom plots

  1. go to biomart b37 and retrieve positions for all hit genes
  • results in file: data/output/S03.hg37_position_hit_genes.2021-01-28.txt
  • manually added entry for RP11-231C18.3 from file /scripts/B_mummy/mummy_genotype/gencode_genes_V25_GRCh37.tsv.gz
  1. create bed file of coding areas awk '{OFS="\t"; print $5, $3, $4, $6, $1}' S03.hg37_position_hit_genes..2021-01-28txt >S03.hg37_position_hit_genes..2021-01-28bed
  2. add window range of 100kb to start and end of gene in new bed file

7.2 load in locuszoom data

> bcac_ref = read.csv(paste0(OUTFOLDER, "S03.locuszoom_regions.2021-01-28.csv"))

7.2.1 reformat locus data

> bcac_ref.format = bcac_ref %>% mutate(cohort = "BCAC_ref", metric = "PValue", P = 10^(-BCAC_study_max_neg_log_P), 
+     P_rank = NA_real_, Hit = NA_character_, is_a_hit = as.character(BCAC_study_hit)) %>% 
+     select(CurrentGene = "GENE", cohort, metric, P, P_rank, Hit, is_a_hit)

8 European hits vs BCAC known

8.1 make plot data

+     "YES")

> eurohit_plot_data = eurohit_plot_data.tmp %>% bind_rows(bcac_ref.format[bcac_ref.format$CurrentGene %in% 
+     eurohit_plot_data.tmp$CurrentGene, ]) %>% left_join(loci, "CurrentGene") %>% 
+     mutate(cohort_fct = recode(cohort, meta.euro = "Euopean\nMeta-Analysis", BCAC_ref = "BCAC\nreplication")) %>% 
+     mutate(Regions_hg38_fct = factor(Regions_hg38, levels = c("chr1:121,167,646-121,185,539",

8.2 qualitive plot (hit vs no-hit)

> eurohit_plot_data %>% ggplot(aes(y = reorder(CurrentGene, Loci), x = fct_relevel(cohort_fct, 
+     "Euopean\nMeta-Analysis"), fill = fct_relevel(is_a_hit, "YES"))) + geom_tile(color = "black") + 
+     my_ggplotTheme + scale_fill_aaas() + facet_wrap(~Regions_hg38_fct, scales = "free_y", 
+     ncol = 1, shrink = F) + labs(title = "European gene hits", subtitle = "Comparing with BCAC results", 
+     x = "Analysis", y = "Gene", fill = "Is gene significant?") + theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank()) + 
+     ggthemr::legend_bottom() + ggsave(paste0(OUTFOLDER, SCRIPT, ".EURO.hits_overlap.qual.LOCI.plus_BCAC_ref.", 
+     DATE, ".pdf"), dpi = 300, device = "pdf", height = 12, width = 6)

8.3 quantiative plot (color by pvalue)

> eurohit_plot_data %>% ggplot(aes(y = reorder(CurrentGene, Loci), x = fct_relevel(cohort_fct, 
+     "Euopean\nMeta-Analysis"), fill = -log10(P))) + geom_tile(color = "black") + 
+     my_ggplotTheme + scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Spectral", direction = 1) + 
+     facet_wrap(~Regions_hg38_fct, scales = "free_y", ncol = 1, shrink = F) + labs(title = "European gene hits", 
+     subtitle = "Comparing with BCAC results", x = "Analysis", y = "Gene", fill = "-log10(P)")  # + 

> ggsave(paste0(OUTFOLDER, SCRIPT, ".EURO.hits_overlap.quanti.LOCI.plus_BCAC_ref.", 
+     DATE, ".pdf"), dpi = 300, device = "pdf", height = 20, width = 8)
